main_food_item: Fried fish with bean stew and boiled root vegetable
cooking_method: Frying (fish), Boiling (root vegetable, beans), Stewing (beans and sauce)

visible_ingredients.name: Fried Fish
visible_ingredients.estimated_quantity: 2 pieces (likely small whole fish or large cuts)

ingredient_breakdown.Fried Fish: Whole Tilapia or similar firm white fish, seasoned with salt, pepper, garlic, and possibly other spices (e.g., paprika), dredged in flour or cornstarch, and deep-fried in vegetable oil or palm oil.
ingredient_breakdown.Boiled Root Vegetable: Chunks of boiled cassava (yuca), yam, or potentially potato, cooked with water and salt.
ingredient_breakdown.Beans: Cooked black-eyed peas or similar light-colored beans, possibly cooked with a small amount of oil and seasoning.
ingredient_breakdown.Stew/Sauce: Tomato-based stew made with blended tomatoes, onions, bell peppers, Scotch bonnet pepper (for heat), garlic, ginger, tomato paste, palm oil (or other vegetable oil), bouillon cube/powder, salt, and various herbs and spices (e.g., thyme, curry powder).

nutritional_info.calories: 800-1200 kcal (estimated, highly dependent on portion size and frying oil absorption)

macros.fats: 40-70g (moderate to high, from fried fish and oil in stew)

nutritional_info.micronutrients: Good source of B vitamins (fish, beans), Vitamin C (tomatoes, peppers), Iron (beans), Potassium (root vegetables, beans), Calcium (fish bones if consumed).
nutritional_info.fiber_content: 15-25g (high, from beans, root vegetable, and vegetables in stew)

allergens: Soy (if soy oil or soy-containing bouillon is used)
dietary_tags: Gluten-Free (if no wheat flour used for fish breading)
additional_notes: This dish is a hearty and complete meal, often found in West African countries like Ghana (where a similar dish with rice and beans is called Waakye), or in Caribbean cuisine. The starchy component appears to be boiled cassava or yam, providing complex carbohydrates. The fish is well-fried and crispy, and the bean stew provides additional protein and fiber, seasoned with a rich, savory, and likely spicy sauce.
